# threejs-engine-dev — Workspace Context

## Role of This Project
This is the **Phase 2 dev harness** for `@base/threejs-engine`. It is a fork of `pwa-shell` used to validate the Three.js engine module before it is consumed by the first game fork.

It will become the starting point for **Phase 4** (first game fork) — game-specific modules will be added here once the engine layer is stable.

## Ecosystem Topology
```
e:/Projects/
  BASE/pwa-shell/             ← shell template this was forked from
  SHARED/packages/
    engine-core/              ← @base/engine-core (linked locally)
    threejs-engine/           ← @base/threejs-engine (linked locally)
  threejs-engine-dev/         ← THIS repo — Three.js engine dev harness
```

## What This Harness Validates
- ThreeModule mounts correctly into ModuleMount slot
- SpinningCubeModule mounts as a child and receives ThreeContext
- registerSystem() drives per-frame rotation
- entity:state-change events fire on setState()
- Navigating away unmounts cleanly with no Three.js disposal warnings

## Code Placement Rules
- Engine improvements → `SHARED/packages/threejs-engine/`
- Shell improvements → `BASE/pwa-shell/`
- Game-specific logic (Phase 4+) → stays in this fork

## Stack
Vue 3 · TypeScript strict · Tailwind CSS · Vue Router · Pinia · Vite
Three.js via `@base/threejs-engine` · locally linked `@base/engine-core`
